\par\pard\plain \tqr\tx10584\li44\fi-43\ri-1829\sa240\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs22\b1\i1\cf3 <$Scr_Cs::3>Note<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f3\fs26\b0\i0 : Scrivener projects are saved onto your hard drive in a folder with the file extension \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93.scriv\u8221\'94. When you create a new project, make sure you know where you are saving it, so that you can locate it in File Explorer. If you ever move to another computer, you\u8217\'92ll want to make sure that you back up and copy your .scriv projects to your new computer.}
\par\plain {\f3\fs26\b0\i0 Although the .scrivx file (with the yellow icon) inside the folder is used to open a project, the entire .scriv folder is the project. Be sure to copy or compress the whole folder when moving the project or creating a zipped backup.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i0 \tab <!$Scr_Ps::2>}
